<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<!--
DOCUMENTATION
	<image></image> 
		the name of the image file from the folder /graphics for example if it is /graphics/monsters/ant.png
		you would put /monsters/ant.png
	<prerot></prerot>
		the rotation correction of the monster image in degrees
	<speed></speed> 
		the speed the monster moves. Player moves at speed=1 for reference
	<attackDelay></attackDelay>
		how many frames elapse between monster attacks. Logic runs at 60hz
	<health></health>
		The health of the enemy, when zero they are destroyed
	<attackRange></attackRange>
		The range(in pixels) at which an enemy will stop chasing and start attacking the player
	<attentionRange></attentionRange>
		The range(in pixels) at which an enemy will start chasing the player. If
		set to -1, the enemy will immediately start chasing the player
	<weapon></weapon>
		The name of the weapon(matching a definition in weapons.xml) the enemy uses
	<sNeutralFrame></sNeutralFrame>
		The starting frame of animation (0,1,2,3,4,...) for movement(will be looped)
	<eNeutralFrame></eNeutralFrame>
		The end frame of animation (0,1,2,3,4,...) for movement(will be looped)
	<sAttackFrame></sAttackFrame>
		Same as above but for attacking animation
	<eAttackFrame></eAttackFrame>
		Same as above but for attacking animation
	<strikeCharge></strikeCharge>
		The strike charge of an enemy(between 0->1) determines how far of maximum a bomb will throw, etc.
	<w></w>
		The width of the enemy image frame
	<h></h>
		The height of the enemy image frame
	<frameCount></frameCount>
		the number of animation frames the enemy has in its image
-->
